{"questionId":"27290","questionHtml":"<p>Find the eigenvalues of the system of coupled first order equations given in part (a).</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>the relevant matrix is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is also possible.</p>\n<p><br>(this has characteristic equation)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27290","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ2.7b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the eigenvalues of the system of coupled first order equations given in part (a).","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}